# Quick Templates & Slider Sync Update Complete!

Your feature requests for the Investor's "Create Goal" Modal have been fully implemented.

## What Was Improved?

### 1. 🤖 Smart Dynamic Quick Templates
The Quick Templates on the left side of the modal are no longer static! They now use an intelligent analysis of the SME's current scores to build dynamic recommendations:

- **Address Critical Risks**: If an SME has pillars in the High Risk/Pre-Investment zones (score < 60), a template automatically appears focusing *only* on pulling those specific weak pillars up to the safe point (65).
- **Push to Investor Ready**: If an SME has pillars stuck in exactly the Near-Ready zone (60-79), a template will appear designed to push those completely over the 80+ threshold.
- **Overall Growth Target**: Regardless of status, an overall growth target appears that attempts a balanced +15 point blanket increase.

Every time you change the selected SME in the dropdown, these templates automatically analyze the newly selected SME and update their logic!

### 2. 🧮 Perfect Pillar Slider Synchronization
The bug where dragging the "Overall Target Score" caused the individual "Pillar Targets" tab to break or not align has been entirely solved natively in Vue:

- When an investor drags an **individual pillar's score slider**, the Overall Target score simply recalculates as a genuine arithmetic average. 
- When an investor grabs the **Overall Component Slider**, a unique proportional distribution algorithm kicks in. Instead of a flat equal `diff` that breaks at the 100 ceiling, the algorithm checks how many target points are allowed for each active pillar (without exceeding 100). It mathematically distributes and "waterfalls" points down so you visually see each pillar smoothly climb up together until they cap naturally.

This means you can now safely bounce between manually editing pillars, clicking Smart Templates, or grabbing the Overall Slider and everything will stay perfectly in sync.

> [!TIP]
> You can try this right now! Log in as your Investor, open the Create Goal modal, and pick an SME. Try clicking the different templates and see how specifically they warp your 8 pillar slider targets based on their risk level!
